# Sub-Agent Sync Workflow

## Canonical Source

- Canonical agents live in `.github/agents/*.agent.md`.
- Target harness folders:
  - `.claude/agents/*.md`
  - `.cursor/agents/*.md`
  - `.gemini/agents/*.md`

## Required Commands

- Drift check:
  - `yarn agents:sync:check`
- Apply sync:
  - `yarn agents:sync`

## Trigger Conditions

Run the sync workflow after any of these:

- Any edit in `.github/agents/**`
- Any edit in `.claude/agents/**`, `.cursor/agents/**`, `.gemini/agents/**`
- Any sub-agent added or removed
- Any sub-agent model changed

## Rules

1. Keep `.github/agents` as canonical source for instruction body content.
2. Preserve existing harness-specific frontmatter where file already exists.
3. Create missing harness files from canonical using harness defaults.
4. Prune extra harness files when canonical file no longer exists (default apply behavior).
5. `CodeExplorer` in Cursor must stay `model: composer`.

## Model Policy

- Cursor defaults: `claude-haiku-4-5`
- Cursor `CodeExplorer`: `composer`
- Prefer low-cost models unless explicit quality needs require a stronger model.
- Keep model mapping centralized in `tools/scripts/sync-subagents.mjs`.

